- "Identifiers" refers to the unique identifiers for each game (`game_id`).;
- "Dates of the games" refers to when each game was played (`date`).;
- "Participants" refers to the players involved in the games (`player_name`).;
- The question seeks information about games and the players who played, which is linked through their shared team identifier (`team_id`).

- In this metaphor, "teams" are referred to as "ships", "conferences" are referred to as "oceans", and "number of games played" is metaphorically translated into "number of miles traveled".;
- "Total number of games" for each team represents the miles traveled by each ship, while the "total number of games" for each conference represents the total miles sailed in each ocean.;
- The "furthest" refers to the teams that have played the most games in their respective conferences.

sql:
SELECT AVG(attendance) AS average_attendance, COUNT(game_id) AS num_games
FROM games
WHERE team_id = 0;

SELECT game_id, opponent_id AS final_challenger
FROM games
ORDER BY margin DESC;
